-------------------------------------------------------------------------

      mk-configure is a lightweight replacement for GNU autoconf,
             written for bmake (NetBSD make).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation:

   make PREFIX=/usr/local
   make install-dirs
   make install

"make" here is (Any)BSD make.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
bmake sources are available from here:
  
There you can also download portable MK scripts (mk-files) for it.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sample: see EXAMPLE.Makefile file.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation: see configure.mk[.in]

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTE: mk-configure is in "beta" stage of development now,
      API may change in the future.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Send your suggestions, bug reports etc. to Aleksey Cheusov <vle@gmx.net>
